---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Nurses | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Nurses working internationally, covering nursing positions abroad, healthcare careers, and global nursing opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Nurses";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Nurses working abroad, providing patient care internationally, and pursuing careers across healthcare systems worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/nurse-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/nurse-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Nurse Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Nurses provide direct patient care, coordinate treatment, educate patients, and serve as the backbone of healthcare delivery. International nursing offers opportunities to work in different healthcare systems, experience diverse patient populations, and develop clinical expertise across global settings.
      </p>
      <p>
        International nursing opportunities exist through hospital recruitment programs, travel nursing agencies, humanitarian organizations, and healthcare systems actively recruiting international nurses.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Nurses working abroad across healthcare systems worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Nurses</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Usually employer-provided' },
          { need: 'Occupational health', why: 'Workplace exposure risks', typical: 'Essential for role' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'Emotional demands of patient care', typical: 'Important for role' },
          { need: 'Ergonomic coverage', why: 'Physical demands of nursing', typical: 'Essential for role' },
          { need: 'Infectious disease', why: 'Pathogen exposure risk', typical: 'Essential for role' },
          { need: 'Wellness support', why: 'Shift work and burnout', typical: 'Often included' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Physical Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Nursing involves significant physical activity—lifting and moving patients, extended standing, repetitive motions, and quick responses. These physical demands create musculoskeletal strain over time. Ergonomic coverage and occupational health support address the physical realities of nursing work.
      </p>
      <p>
        Back injuries remain one of the most common occupational health issues for nurses worldwide.
      </p>

      <h3>Emotional Labor</h3>
      <p>
        Nurses witness suffering, death, and family trauma regularly. The emotional demands of patient care, combined with staffing pressures and patient expectations, create significant mental health demands. Mental health support helps nurses process the emotional weight of caregiving.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Hospital</h3>
      <p>
        Acute care hospital. Hospital benefits. Clinical variety. Hospitals offer experience.
      </p>

      <h3>Travel Nursing</h3>
      <p>
        Travel nursing agency. Agency benefits. Assignment variety. Travel offers flexibility.
      </p>

      <h3>Humanitarian</h3>
      <p>
        NGO or humanitarian organization. Organization benefits. Challenging environments. Humanitarian offers purpose.
      </p>

      <h3>Private Clinic</h3>
      <p>
        International clinic or practice. Clinic benefits. Specialty focus. Clinics offer balance.
      </p>

      <h3>Cruise/Remote</h3>
      <p>
        Cruise ship or remote site nursing. Specialized benefits. Unique environment. Remote offers adventure.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Nurses"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Nurses working abroad across healthcare systems worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Nurse Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Nursing License</h3>
      <p>
        RN or equivalent credential. Jurisdictional licensing. Practice authorization. License typically required.
      </p>

      <h3>Credential Recognition</h3>
      <p>
        License verification process. Credential evaluation. Bridging programs. Recognition varies by country.
      </p>

      <h3>Specialty Certification</h3>
      <p>
        ICU, OR, pediatric specialties. Advanced practice credentials. Specialty training. Certifications add value.
      </p>

      <h3>Language Proficiency</h3>
      <p>
        Patient communication essential. Language testing required. Medical terminology. Language skills critical.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Physical Strain</h3>
      <p>
        Patient handling. Extended standing. Repetitive motions. Ergonomic coverage essential.
      </p>

      <h3>Exposure Risks</h3>
      <p>
        Infectious diseases. Needlestick injuries. Chemical exposure. Occupational health critical.
      </p>

      <h3>Emotional Burden</h3>
      <p>
        Patient suffering. Death exposure. Family interactions. Mental health support important.
      </p>

      <h3>Shift Work</h3>
      <p>
        Night shifts. Rotating schedules. Extended hours. Wellness support valuable.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Direct Care</h3>
      <p>
        Patient assessment. Treatment administration. Care coordination. Direct care saves lives.
      </p>

      <h3>Documentation</h3>
      <p>
        Medical records. Care planning. Compliance requirements. Documentation ensures continuity.
      </p>

      <h3>Communication</h3>
      <p>
        Patient education. Family updates. Team coordination. Communication enables care.
      </p>

      <h3>Emergency Response</h3>
      <p>
        Critical situations. Rapid assessment. Intervention delivery. Response protects patients.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Excellent Demand</h3>
      <p>
        Global nursing shortage. Aging populations. Healthcare expansion. Demand excellent worldwide.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Charge Nurse. Nurse Manager. Nurse Practitioner. Nurse Educator. Multiple paths available.
      </p>

      <h3>Credential Portability</h3>
      <p>
        Nursing skills universal. Licensing specific. Verification required. Core skills transfer well.
      </p>

      <h3>Field Evolution</h3>
      <p>
        Technology integration. Expanded scope. Advanced practice growth. Field evolving continuously.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a nurse considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Healthcare employers typically provide benefits. Licensing varies significantly. Credential verification required. Nursing skills transfer.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do employers provide international coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Healthcare employers typically yes. Travel nursing includes benefits. Humanitarian often comprehensive. Verify occupational health coverage.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Are physical demands a significant concern?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes in nursing. Patient handling intensive. Ergonomic coverage essential. Back injury common.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do nursing credentials transfer internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Core skills yes. Licensing specific to jurisdiction. Verification required. Bridging programs available.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is burnout a significant concern?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes in nursing. Emotional demands high. Staff shortages add stress. Mental health support important.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Global shortage continuing. Demand excellent everywhere. Opportunities abundant. Outlook outstanding.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by evaluating employer benefits packages. Prioritize occupational health coverage for workplace risks. Ensure ergonomic support for physical demands. Verify mental health coverage for emotional demands.
      </p>
      <p>
        Nurses provide essential care worldwide. Your coverage should support nursing careers—addressing physical and emotional demands, covering occupational health, and protecting you across healthcare work worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Nursing Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Nurses working abroad across healthcare systems worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
